      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLUE BIDDY (5) stalked the pace then went home a shade too well on debut last start over 800m at Narromine. Looks well placed over an extra 200m today so with a bit of natural improvement another victory is on the cards. PANTA RHEI (2) is back after a break of seven months. Only raced once last prep and was edged out over this distance at Tamworth. Honest mare who should play a key role again while fresh. BARON OF BUTTER (4) was turned out after winning his maiden over this distance at Dubbo on 2 February. Lightly raced four-year-old back for a second campaign. Should be right in contention. CHAPPOLICIOUS (6) has been about the mark at his last couple in weaker company. Nicely in after the claim and the addition of blinkers might be significant. TROPIC (3) has disappointed in two runs this prep but is capable of a lot better.",
